# Notes TurboAI — Cursor Rules

## Commit convention
- Use Conventional Commits: `type(scope): message`
- Scope must match: `IZ-\d+`, `infra`, or a feature slug

## Code style
- DRY: never duplicate business logic or UI patterns — extract to a function/component
- No obvious comments (avoid "# increment counter", "// return result")
- Python: ruff-formatted, typed (mypy strict), no bare except
- TypeScript: strict mode, no `any`, prefer `unknown` + narrowing

## Backend (`backend/`)
- All app code lives under `backend/apps/`
- Authentication: `CognitoJWTAuthentication` — never use Django sessions or SimpleJWT
- Models use `cognito_sub` (UUID) as the per-user key, never a FK to auth.User for notes/categories
- API responses are JSON; errors follow `{ "detail": "..." }` DRF convention
- Always run `ruff check . --fix` and `mypy .` before declaring done

## Frontend (`frontend/`)
- App Router only — no Pages Router patterns
- All state-changing API calls go through `/api/auth/*` or `/api/*` Next.js Route Handlers (never direct to Django)
- No secrets or tokens in client-side code or `localStorage`
- Components in `src/components/`, hooks in `src/hooks/`, lib in `src/lib/`
- Always run `npm run typecheck` and `npm run lint -- --quiet` before declaring done

## Infra (`infra/`)
- Terraform modules in `infra/modules/`
- Never hardcode secrets — use SSM Parameter Store or Secrets Manager
- Tag all resources with `Project=notes`, `Env=var.env`
